ExploreRules1: * The difficulty of exploration determines your resource reward acquisition coefficient, and will also match opponents with different strengths according to the difficulty in the encounter. If the encounter fails, part of the mined resources will be deducted, but it can be obtained by placing it in the planet. Put the cellar to reduce losses.
ExploreRules3: * According to your own positioning, reasonable management of planetary buildings and placement of troops will lead to better results.
ExploreRules4: * Reasonable management of planets will strengthen your combat ability.
ExploreRules5: * Combat deployment strategies can also make you stand out.
PlayRules1: * Planetary Alliance is the basic unit to participate in interstellar exploration and occupation of stars. A Planetary Alliance consists of five and only five planets
PlayRules2: * Through interstellar exploration, the buildings on the planet will all be in working condition, for example: resource buildings will start to work, and the army training base will start training troops... At the same time, each building will also be consumed synchronously. resources to maintain working conditions.
PlayRules3: * It should be reminded that choosing different difficulties will get different resource reward coefficients. At the same time, according to the difficulty, you will also select alliances with different strengths that are engaged in interstellar exploration to trigger encounters. Victory will plunder more resources. If you fail, a part of the resources will be deducted from the winner.
PlayRules4: * When you start exploring, the first 1.5 hours is the protection period, and the second 2.5 hours into the war space may trigger encounters
PlayRules5: * During the encounter, the planets in the planetary alliance will be randomly selected for battle. According to the battle results, various resources will be gained/lost. Failure to fight will consume durability.
PlayRules6: * A total of 4 hours of exploration, start your interstellar exploration!
